HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 321
BY REPRESENTATIVE FREEMAN
DOMESTIC ABUSE: Requests the Louisiana Commission on Law Enforcement and
Administration of Criminal Justice to receive input, feedback, and suggestions
relative to uniform protocols for examinations for survivors of domestic violence
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Louisiana Commission on Law Enforcement and Administration of
3 Criminal Justice to conduct a comprehensive review of the statutory framework and
4 administrative procedures in order to establish uniform protocols for forensic
5 medical examinations for survivors of domestic violence and to provide a consistent
6 source of reimbursement for these examinations.
7 WHEREAS, the state of Louisiana is committed to protecting the safety and
8 well-being of all its citizens, particularly those who are victims of domestic and family
9 violence; and
10 WHEREAS, domestic violence, including acts of strangulation and physical battery,
11 often results in internal injuries and forensic evidence that requires specialized medical
12 expertise for identification, documentation, and preservation; and
13 WHEREAS, while forensic medical examinations are a standardized component of
14 the response to sexually oriented criminal offenses, a similar uniform standard for survivors
15 of domestic violence is currently lacking in many jurisdictions across the state; and
16 WHEREAS, the lack of uniform protocols for domestic violence forensic
17 examinations leads to inconsistencies in evidence collection, which can impede the
18 successful prosecution of offenders and the ability of victims to secure protective orders; and
