HR 321 Original 2026 Regular Session Freeman
Requests the Louisiana Commission on Law Enforcement and Administration of Criminal
Justice (LCLE) to conduct a comprehensive review of the statutory framework and
administrative procedures in order to establish uniform protocols for forensic medical
examinations for survivors of domestic violence and to provide a consistent source of
reimbursement for these examinations.
Requires the LCLE to submit a written report of its findings and recommendations to the
House Committee on Administration of Criminal Justice no later than 60 days prior to the
start of the 2027 R.S. of the Legislature of La.
